Hurricane Floyd vented its fury on the Bahamas on Tuesday -- toppling trees and power lines, stripping roofs off homes and shoving a roiling sea into streets.
American Airlines canceled its nine daily flights between southern Florida and its hub in San Juan, Puerto Rico, while both Carnival Cruise Lines and Royal Caribbean Cruise Lines sent Bahamas-bound ships to Mexico instead.
Officials expected storm surges up to 20 feet and warned they could flood areas of New Providence six miles inland -- a daunting prospect for an island seven miles wide.
